# FinPay Walkthrough — Sprints 1–3

## Sprint 1: Infrastructure ✅
Multi-module Maven project: `api-parent` → `common`, `payment-service`, `webhook-service`, `analytics-service` on Spring Boot 3.2.5.

## Sprint 2: Data Layer ✅
JPA entities ([Merchant](file:///d:/DEVS/ANTIGRAVITY/FINTECH/FinPay/apps/api/common/src/main/java/com/finpay/common/entities/Merchant.java#8-39), [Transaction](file:///d:/DEVS/ANTIGRAVITY/FINTECH/FinPay/apps/api/common/src/main/java/com/finpay/common/entities/Transaction.java#8-58), [WebhookEvent](file:///d:/DEVS/ANTIGRAVITY/FINTECH/FinPay/apps/api/common/src/main/java/com/finpay/common/entities/WebhookEvent.java#8-50)) with Lombok, UUID IDs, `@PrePersist` timestamps. Flyway V1 migration script.

## Sprint 3: Core Payment API ✅

### Architecture

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    Client->>PaymentController: POST /v1/payments
    PaymentController->>PaymentService: createPayment(request)
    PaymentService->>TransactionRepository: findByIdempotencyKey()
    alt Already exists
        TransactionRepository-->>PaymentService: existing tx
    else New payment
        PaymentService->>TransactionRepository: save(PENDING)
        PaymentService->>StripeService: createPaymentIntent()
        StripeService->>Stripe API: PaymentIntent.create()
        Stripe API-->>StripeService: PaymentIntent
        PaymentService->>TransactionRepository: save(status update)
    end
    PaymentService-->>PaymentController: PaymentResponse
    PaymentController-->>Client: 201 Created
```

